# loan-shark-escape-env

Reinforcement-learning style environment for training agentic AI to navigate and escape predatory loan scenarios (OpenEnv).

## Layout (Person 1 — environment + server)

```text
loan-shark-escape-env/
├── server/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── app.py              # FastAPI server
│   ├── environment.py      # Core simulation logic
│   └── Dockerfile
├── tasks/
│   ├── lse-easy.json
│   ├── lse-medium.json
│   └── lse-hard.json
├── __init__.py
├── models.py               # Pydantic data models
├── openenv.yaml            # OpenEnv manifest
├── pyproject.toml
├── requirements.txt
├── .env.example
├── .gitignore
└── README.md
```

## Quick start

```bash
cd loan-shark-escape-env
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -e .
uvicorn server.app:app --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
```

Health check: `GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/health`

## Docker

```bash
docker build -t loan-shark-escape-env -f server/Dockerfile .
docker run -p 8000:8000 loan-shark-escape-env
```

Person 2 deliverables (`client.py`, `grader.py`, `inference.py`, `demo.ipynb`) are intentionally omitted from this branch.
